  "updated_summary": "In the simulated Emirates FA Cup final at Wembley Stadium, with Manchester City trailing Manchester United 4-5 deep into stoppage time past 101 minutes, commentators noted the rarity of such a high-scoring game. Manchester City's 26 Mahrez and 20 Silva attempted to build an attack, but Manchester United's 8 Fernandes and 6 Fred executed a strong interception. Manchester City's 9 Haaland received the ball near the penalty area and took a shot, which was saved by Manchester United's goalkeeper, David de Gea. As the match entered its final minute of stoppage time, a substitution occurred: 39 McTominay replaced 8 Bruno Fernandes for Manchester United. The game resumed with Manchester City's 10 Grealish and 26 Mahrez trying to create chances against Manchester United's defense, while the animated Stadium Crowd roared. Grealish attempted a shot from the edge of the box, but it was cleared. The match then saw a dramatic turn as Manchester City, despite a shot saved by the Manchester United goalkeeper, scored from the rebound following a poor clearance, leveling the score at 5-5 at 105:00 minutes, with the first period of extra time concluding shortly after."
